{
  "stem": "11274.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Jewish children could leave, had the privilege to leave the school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And on Saturday there were classes, too, half a day, because Wednesday was a half a day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's why Saturday they had a half a day of school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Jewish children were free to stay home because of the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't write on the Sabbath, and we couldn't carry things on the Sabbath because that was a small town.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were no telephone wires around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It has to be closed in, in order to carry something, even a handkerchief.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Hasidic Orthodox Jews' rules were that you don't carry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "If you wanted a handkerchief, you tied it around your wrist to wear it, and no carrying no money or anything.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we could-- we didn't-- so the homework, the teacher was so nice, all the teachers, the nun, too, that there was never given on Saturday.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Always the homework for the weekend was given on Friday so the Jewish children could do the homework on Sunday before we came to school.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it couldn't be any, any nicer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Just wonderful memories from it, that we lived in peace.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, and during the war, as I said, they couldn't deal with Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But if you-- they allowed us, if we were working, handwork, doing something for a Gentile, then we could get something for it, either money or, or food for it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and my older sister Zosia escaped during--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While later on, after the, the Germans came in and they forbid us all proclamations for the-- no-- no going to-- we couldn't go to a doctor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took away all the privileges from us that free people have, going to a doctor, seeing a dentist.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You couldn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
